The paper uses a network approach based on Twitter data to analyze the topics of tweeted publications and compare them with the topics of all publications. This involves analyzing the topics of climate change research, which could fall under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper focuses on analyzing social media data and using a network approach. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper involves analyzing and categorizing large amounts of data related to climate change research.
